race.comment: MADHI GIRL (6) went huge during a winter campaign, and has returned without missing a beat, scoring fresh up by a head here 9 days ago in the Summer Scorcher Stakes over 1000m, taking her winning streak to 4 on the bounce. William Pike sticks with her, and so do we. RICHANCO (11) finished third behind the top pick in the same race at his second run back from a spell. He will be peaking for this, and with the aid of the pole position, he should go close to taking this out, especially with only 54kg to carry again. WIND AND THE LION (5) resumes from a spell that would have done him the world of good. He was good enough to win at this level in July, and even without a trial, he is expected to sprint well fresh up. Check the markets. SINFUL LIVING (12) is closing in on another win and CUT THE TALK (7) is capable at this level on his best day. Include both in all top 4 combos.
